text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described in 1873 by Ferdinand von Mueller and the description was published in Fragmenta phytographiae Australiae. The specific epithet (gilesii) honours Ernest Giles who collected the type specimen.There are two subspecies:

Eremophila gilesii  F.Muell.  subsp. gilesii which has distinctly flattened flower stalks and linear leaves and is the more widespread subspecies;
Eremophila gilesii subsp. variabilis  Chinnock  which has flower stalks that are only slightly flattened in the lower part, elliptic to lance-shaped leaves and is only found in Western Australia.
